I had a situation where I was asked to allow users to filter data with regex (usually not a good idea, but it was necessary.) I was going to restrict the amount of times that a pattern could recurse (which needed more work on my part) so that users can't DoS the server. But somebody else interjected to suggest that we don't bother limiting it unless a problem shows up. And ul<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
