		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64641740"><p>Basically, the issue is organizations not providing time, tools and resources to harden systems. It's easier to just punt the problem onto the OS or security software. It's not a matter of training developers to do better. The obvious blunders most developers know about and there are tools that will find them easily.</p><p>Many software vulnerabilities come from complex interactions that are really hard to find without a lot of expert knowledge, dedicated resources and time.</p><p>Basically, the amount of code out there<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64641740">

